## §5 Director/Captain/Builder/Worker hierarchy — Employ the World canon

**Fresh-mint candidates.** Pheromone hits found in Bishop Toolsmith (match_strength 2) and KnightQueue (match_strength up to 3 for Bounty Poster context) but no named canon slugs. Formal pearl emit recommended at next session.

### Founder direct

> "EVERYTHING needs Directors, Captains, and Builders, and Workers."

This is part of "Employ the World" — canonical 16-initiative #3 per BP078 memory. The Bounty Poster is the canonical mechanism for posting these roles publicly.

### Role definitions (candidate, pending Founder ratify)

- **Director** — program-level ownership. Sets vision and scope. Accountable for outcomes. Analogous to a non-profit Executive Director or corporate VP. One Director per program (Santa Ever After, Let's Make Dinner, etc.).
- **Captain** — initiative-level lead within a program. Runs day-to-day. Reports to Director. Owns a specific initiative or vertical.
- **Builder** — creates and makes the actual deliverables. Ships work. Owns craft output.
- **Worker** — executes tasks within Builder's scope. Entry tier. Learns the craft. Earns feathers.

### Composition with existing canon

- `canon_workers_builders_creators_keep_83_3` — Workers and Builders ARE the keeping-83.3% class. Directors and Captains are governance and coordination tier. Compensation structure for the upper tiers is TBD ratify; must compose with cooperative-class governance and Threefold Cord mentorship.
- `canon_six_veterans_leadership_starship_troopers_foot_washing_bp051` — service-before-leadership: Directors and Captains must have done Builder or Worker tier first. Graduated cooperative-class governance pipeline. You do not direct what you have not built.

### Bounty Poster surface

Bounty Poster Offerings is the canonical mechanism for posting Director/Captain/Builder/Worker roles publicly. Pheromone index returned a KnightQueue hit at match_strength 3 (tablet KnightQueue_1848) — strongest single hit across all 7 gadget queries in this session. The surface exists in scope but a dedicated Bounty Poster component for public posting of Director-class roles may not yet be built. Knight scopes in Wave E.

