## §6 Santa Ever After — 12-tier Stripe products live, awaiting Program Director

**Truth-Always state as of 2026-06-10.**

### Stripe products confirmed (test mode, screenshot-verified)

Annual tiers:
- CULTIVATOR Annual — $1,000
- GARDENER Annual — $100
- SEEDLING Annual — $25

Monthly tiers:
- CULTIVATOR Monthly — $100
- GARDENER Monthly — $10
- SEEDLING Monthly — amount to verify (not captured in screenshot)

One-time tiers:
- SPONSOR — $250
- INFERNO — $50
- BLAZE — $30
- FLAME — $15
- KINDLE — $5
- SPARK — $1

Total: 12 tiers (11 confirmed amounts, 1 to verify).

### Metaphor pattern (canon candidate)

Garden tier (cultivation metaphor): CULTIVATOR, GARDENER, SEEDLING — growth, nurturing, long-horizon giving. Annual and monthly recurring.

Fire tier (kindling metaphor): INFERNO, BLAZE, FLAME, KINDLE, SPARK — ignition, one-time momentum, immediate energy.

Flat anchor: SPONSOR — $250 one-time, mid-range, no metaphor tier; functions as a named sponsorship level.

### Gate

Santa Ever After CANNOT ship operationally until a Program Director is hired. Founder direct: "EVERYTHING needs Directors." The 12 Stripe products exist and are valid. No operational program runs them yet. No charitable allocation happens. No donor receives recognition or impact reporting. The products are infrastructure waiting for a human director.

### Bounty Poster action needed

Post the Santa Ever After Program Director role on the canonical Bounty Poster surface. If no dedicated Director-class Bounty Poster component exists yet, queue for Wave E build. Role criteria for the Director post (draft, pending Founder ratify):
- Has done Builder or Worker tier work in a prior cooperative-class context (service-before-leadership canon)
- Accountable for: donor experience, charitable allocation process, impact reporting to donors, seasonal campaign calendar (Santa Ever After = seasonal by name)
- Reports to: Founder (until governance structure matures)
- Compensation: cooperative-class structure, TBD ratify

